    "id": "post_300",
    "images": [
      "18110883925070141.jpg"
    ],
    "caption": "We had such a lovely weekend.\n\nRobyn smashed two whole minutes of her PB at Parkrun (down to 33 mins now). Homework, then Brunch. Dilly requested \"three bowls of porridge\". Then the whole team did our laundry and cleaned the house. They both are so helpful.\n\nWe made lemon vegan cupcakes, which turned out great. I love the earnest, scientific accuracy the Dilly applies to the measurements.\n\nIn the evening, we watched The Red Turtle, which is a #studioghibli\nanimation about a man stranded on an island. It's silent and I wasn't sure if it would hole their attention, but all three of us thought it was poignant and beautiful.\n\nSunday saw us doing Junior Parkrun. Both girls tried really hard. Dilly got 11:41 and Robyn got 12:11, which is a PB for both of them.\n\nAfter more homework and porridge we got in the car to take Dilly to a party in Croydon and Robyn and I wandered around Costco. She feels so grown up that it's lovely just to hang out together doing mundane stuff chatting.\n\nWhen I got home, I meal prepped the week's dinners and then crashed in front of the telly.",
