    "caption": "Sunday afternoon reading with cake and coffee\n\nDilly is reading \"The World's Worst Teachers\" by David Walliams. She's chortling out loud every few minutes, so I think it's good.\n\nRobyn is reading \"Sky Circus\" by Peter Bunzl (3rd in the Cogheart Trilogy that she has loved.\n\nI am reading James O'Brien's \"How to be right in a world gone wrong\". I'm a fan of his radio show, but so far it's pretty self agrandising and hasn't made any points other than the political beyond the initial observation that questions are highly effective way of getting someone to lay out the fallacy in what they're saying.",
