    "id": "post_376",
    "images": [
      "17853277486328211.jpg"
    ],
    "caption": "The irony of posting this on social hasn't escaped me, but this book is convincing me that I need to minimally make some changes but more realistically (and I'm leaning towards this) quitting the Facebook empire.\n\nI have long known that Twitter is bad for my mental health, but I'm somehow not yet ready to quit - it has one thing over Facebook and that's that it's interesting. \nIt's a shame because I really enjoy Instagram and WhatsApp has been very useful as a communications tool. It also feels like a scary leap to make... \"Will I hear from people ever again?\" is a nagging worry, but maybe a leap of faith is required.\n\nGoing to sit with the decision until the end of the book.",
    "timestamp": 1548500264,
    "date": "2019-01-26"
