    "id": "post_478",
    "images": [
      "17850467164197768.jpg"
    ],
    "caption": "I spent my Saturday morning building a bit more of my Lego Ideas #NASA #SaturnV, drinking coffee and listening to #TED talks in the background.\n\nThe second stage of the rocket is now done. It's fascinating building it as there's incredible intricacy inside that eventually gets hidden behind black and white panels. I find myself often thinking \"I wonder where's this going...\" and a page or two later it becomes clearer. Though I'm not 100% sure if the elaborate shapes and colours inside are there to make it feel more like the inside of a complex rocket or just to make it more interesting to build.\n\nIf you've not built any Lego since childhood, I strongly recommend having a go. It feels genuinely calming and therapeutic.",
